The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	 Calcutta, Sept. 20: K. Keshava Rao, the Congress in-charge for Bengal, has assured the Trinamul Congress that senior state Congress leaders would not meddle in the Siliguri mayor selection, which would be done at the local level.    
	I have assured Mukulji (Roy) that neither the high command nor senior state Congress leaders would intervene in the choice of the mayor for the Siliguri civic board. The matter will be left to local councillors of both the parties, Rao said today over phone from Hyderabad.        
	 Calcutta: Three men were arrested at Ernakulam station for allegedly molesting girls of Calcuttas Jogmaya Devi College who had gone for an excursion to Kerala. Railway sources said 58 girls and 11 staff members were on their way back from Kerala on the Gurudev Express. They said the men passed lewd remarks at the girls and also molested some of them when the train was between Kottayam and Ernakulam stations. When the train reached Ernakulam, the girls lodged a complaint to get the men arrested.        
	Santiniketan: Author Mahasweta Devi, painters Jogen Chowdhury and Suvaprasanna have demanded a CBI probe into the building of an amusement park on the outskirts of Santiniketan that was to be inaugurated on Sunday. They protested near the park with 200 people, saying the park would pollute the Visva-Bharati campus. The opening of the park has been put off.         
	Durgapur: Twenty armed robbers beat up moneylender Lakshman Bahadur on Saturday night after raiding his house in Kulti, Burdwan. When Lakshmans elder brother Ranjit came to his rescue, the gang hurled bombs at him. The robbers also hurled bombs at villagers who rushed in. Three villagers sustained splinter injuries.         
	Bolpur: Sheikh Babu Mian, 25, was beaten to death on Sunday afternoon by two men after an altercation in Bolpur town of Birbhum, about 190 km from Calcutta. Police said a neighbour, Sheikh Alam, and his son Nayeem were arrested.                                                                                                                                                                        
